# International Mathematical Olympiad 2010, Problem 3

Determine all functions g : ‚Ą§>0 ‚Üí ‚Ą§>0 such that

               (g(m) + n)(g(n) + m)

is always a perfect square.
-/

namespace Imo2010P3

abbrev PosInt : Type := { x : ‚Ą§ // 0 < x }

notation "‚Ą§>0" => PosInt

determine SolutionSet : Set (‚Ą§>0 ‚Üí ‚Ą§>0) := { f | f = id ‚ą® ‚ąÉ c, ‚ąÄ x, f x = x + c }

problem imo2010_p3 (g : ‚Ą§>0 ‚Üí ‚Ą§>0) :
    g ‚ąą SolutionSet ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ m n, IsSquare ((g m + n) * (g n + m)) := by
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro (rfl | ‚ü®c, hc‚ü©) m n
    ¬∑ use m + n; rw [id, id, add_comm m n]
    ¬∑ use m + n + c; simp_all [add_assoc, add_comm, add_left_comm]
